column1: I agree to participate in the research project under the conditions described above.
column2: Please create your own nickname. *PLEASE* make sure you remember this in 28 days as we do not keep this information for anonymization purpose. This identifier will *ONLY* be used for matching the feedback of post-intervention questionnaire.
column3: Are you a Software Engineering (SE) student or working in the SE field ?
column4: How many years have you participated in SE project development/worked in SE? (You can put 0 if you are a SE student.)
column5: What roles do you play in SE project development/work in SE ? (You can put NA if this does't apply to you.)
column6: What is your current residence country/region?
column7: Have you practiced mindful relaxation continuously and usually in the past 14 days? ( If YES, you do not meet our sampling criteria -> we still appreciate your interest)
column8: In terms of stress level, on a scale from 1-5, using only integers, how would you rate your stress arising from your work or any events directly related to your work on a working day?
column9: In terms of focus level, on a scale from 1-5, using only integers, how much do you focus on your current work, with mind at present?
column10: When you received newly assigned tasks, how often do you feel fully occupied?
column11: How often do you feel you are competent and capable when handling tasks?
column12: How often do you feel it is difficult to stay focused on what’s happening in the present?
column13: How often do you feel stressed out when you encountered unknown errors?
column14: How often do you not concentrate enough on your work?
column15: How often do you find yourself not working as carefully as you should?
column16: How often do you experience some emotion and not be conscious of it until some time later?
column17: How often do you get so focused on the goaI you want to achieve that Iose touch with what you are doing right now to get there?
column18: Using the same 0-to-10 scale, how would you rate your overall job performance on the days you worked during the past 4 weeks (28 days)?
column19: When received newly assigned tasks, I will handle it as smoothly as I can.
column20: When formulating commit messages, I can remember exactly what I have modified.
column21: When taking a break, my mind is still always full of technical issues.
column22: How often do you do no work at times when you are supposed to be working?
column23: How do you find communicating  with teammates when collaborating on fixes?
